{"TopicId":212247,"ForumId":112,"TopicTitle":"Gizmos for procedural parts","CreatedByName":"Vl3d","CreatedById":219348,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-02-23T16:52:20Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"Vl3d","CreatedById":219348,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-02-23T16:52:20Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nRight now the size and shape parameters of the procedural wings are controlled through sliders in the Part Manager. It would be great to be able to control them directly using gizmos that pop up when selecting the wing. Just like we have for position and orientation (which by the way.. I think the color coding should be different for rotation and position).\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022wing-gizmos.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 data-ratio=\u002267.83\u0022 height=\u0022312\u0022 width=\u0022460\u0022 src=\u0022https://i.ibb.co/gZwtYMg/wing-gizmos.png\u0022\u003E\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0 \u003Cimg alt=\u0022vab-rotation-position-gizmos.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage ipsAttachLink_image\u0022 data-ratio=\u002262.20\u0022 height=\u0022515\u0022 style=\u0022width:500px;height:auto;\u0022 width=\u0022829\u0022 src=\u0022https://i.ibb.co/T4TnBkG/vab-rotation-position-gizmos.png\u0022\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222023-02-23T16:53:00Z\u0022 title=\u002202/23/2023 04:53  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00221 yr\u0022\u003EFebruary 23, 2023\u003C/time\u003E by Vl3d\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"jastrone","CreatedById":208489,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-02-23T17:08:12Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224238897\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022212247\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221677171140\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022219348\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Vl3d\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n11 minutes ago, Vl3d said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n(which by the way.. I think the color coding should be different for rotation and position).\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nthats kinda stupid. the whole point of color coding is that you can see the ones that are the same axis. green arow to move on the x axis and green turned arrow to rotate around the x axis for example. this is really helpfull when the perspective doesnt really show you a whole arraw because its behind the other ones or itself\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"whatsEJstandfor","CreatedById":220814,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-02-23T18:52:23Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224238897\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022212247\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221677171140\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022219348\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Vl3d\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 hour ago, Vl3d said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0(which by the way.. I think the color coding should be different for rotation and position).\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://i.ibb.co/gZwtYMg/wing-gizmos.png\u0022 title=\u0022Enlarge image\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022wing-gizmos.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage ipsImage_thumbnailed\u0022 data-ratio=\u002267.83\u0022 height=\u0022312\u0022 width=\u0022460\u0022 src=\u0022https://i.ibb.co/gZwtYMg/wing-gizmos.png\u0022\u003E\u003C/a\u003E\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0\u00A0 \u003Ca href=\u0022https://i.ibb.co/T4TnBkG/vab-rotation-position-gizmos.png\u0022 title=\u0022Enlarge image\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022vab-rotation-position-gizmos.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage ipsAttachLink_image ipsImage_thumbnailed\u0022 data-ratio=\u002262.20\u0022 height=\u0022515\u0022 style=\u0022width:500px;height:auto;\u0022 width=\u0022829\u0022 src=\u0022https://i.ibb.co/T4TnBkG/vab-rotation-position-gizmos.png\u0022\u003E\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt\u0027s been kind of an unofficial standard for decades for 3D editors to use green for the Y-axis, blue for the Z-axis, and red for the X-axis, and for rot/trans/scale controls about those axes to be those colors. I don\u0027t think there\u0027s a good reason to change it. It gives an intuitive way to know \u0022if I drag the blue straight arrow, it moves along Z. If I drag the curved blue arrow, it rotates about Z\u0022\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Vl3d","CreatedById":219348,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-02-23T18:57:41Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOkay, hope it will not be confusing and I can easily pick between two arrows that have the same color. Opinions about the procedural (parts) wings gizmos?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Bej Kerman","CreatedById":182413,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-02-23T19:00:39Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe KSP 2 gizmo is fine, I just think Squad\u0027s design made it much easier to tell the rotation handles apart from transformation.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}